<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7661/6.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-03"><hi rend="italic">August 3,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Beaupré states that matters have been arranged so that he thinks
                            there will be no more difficulty concerning the admission of deviled
                            ham.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>